@module lexer
@lang aria
@aid_version 0.2
@layer 2
@purpose Tokenizes Aria source code into a stream of typed tokens
@depends [diagnostic]
@workflow First stage of the compilation pipeline. Produces a token list consumed by the parser. All subsequent stages depend on correct tokenization.
@invariants
  Token list always starts with a sentinel TkEof at index 0 (from new_lexer initialization) and ends with a TkEof appended by tokenize.
  Newline tokens are only inserted outside parentheses and brackets (not braces), and only after tokens that terminate statements.
  The lexer is purely functional — all state transitions produce a new Lexer struct rather than mutating in place.

---

@type TokenKind
@kind sum
@variants
  TkIdent — Identifier
  TkIntLit — Integer literal
  TkFloatLit — Float literal
  TkStringLit — String literal
  TkCharLit — Character literal
  TkBoolTrue — true keyword
  TkBoolFalse — false keyword
  TkRawStringLit — Raw string r"..."
  TkTripleStringLit — Triple-quoted string
  TkDurationLit — Duration literal
  TkSizeLit — Size literal
  TkStringStart — Start of interpolated string
  TkStringMiddle — Middle segment of interpolated string
  TkStringEnd — End of interpolated string
  TkMod — mod keyword
  TkUse — use keyword
  TkPub — pub keyword
  TkFn — fn keyword
  TkType — type keyword
  TkEnum — enum keyword
  TkTrait — trait keyword
  TkImpl — impl keyword
  TkStruct — struct keyword
  TkEntry — entry keyword
