@fn _is_alpha_num
@sig (c: str) -> bool
@source_file src/lexer/lexer.aria
@source_line 43
@purpose Tests if a character is alphanumeric or underscore. Used for identifier continuation characters.

---

@fn _is_whitespace
@sig (c: str) -> bool
@source_file src/lexer/lexer.aria
@source_line 45
@purpose Tests if a character is horizontal whitespace (space, tab, carriage return). Newlines are NOT whitespace here — they are handled separately for statement termination.
@notes Deliberate exclusion of \n: newline handling is semantic in Aria (it can produce TkNewline tokens), so it must be processed by the main tokenize loop, not skipped as whitespace. [src: lexer.aria:44]

