@fn _peek_next
@sig (lex: Lexer) -> str
@source_file src/lexer/lexer.aria
@source_line 92
@purpose Returns the character one position ahead of current without advancing. Used for two-character operator lookahead (e.g., distinguishing `=` from `==` and `=>`).
@post Returns a single-character string, or "" if pos+1 is at or past end.

