@fn _advance
@sig (lex: Lexer) -> Lexer
@source_file src/lexer/lexer.aria
@source_line 101
@purpose Moves the lexer forward by one byte, incrementing pos and col. Does NOT handle newlines — use _newline for \n characters.
@post pos incremented by 1, col incremented by 1. All other state preserved.
@antipatterns Do not call _advance on a \n character; it will increment col instead of resetting it. Use _newline which resets col to 1 and increments line. [src: lexer.aria:202-216]

