@fn _add_error
@sig (lex: Lexer, code: str, message: str) -> Lexer
@source_file src/lexer/lexer.aria
@source_line 140
@purpose Records a lexer error diagnostic at the current position with a span of length 1. Uses diagnostic module's new_span and bag_add_error.
@effects Adds one error to diagnostics bag. Does not halt scanning — the lexer continues to produce tokens after errors.
@notes Error codes used: E0001 (unexpected character), E0002 (unterminated string/raw string literal). [src: lexer.aria:801, 425, 461, 498]

