@fn _in_delimiters
@sig (lex: Lexer) -> bool
@source_file src/lexer/lexer.aria
@source_line 158
@purpose Tests whether the lexer is inside parentheses or brackets (but NOT braces). When true, newlines are suppressed — they are not converted to TkNewline tokens.
@notes Braces are intentionally excluded. In Aria, `{ }` blocks need newlines for statement separation, but `( )` and `[ ]` allow multi-line expressions without statement breaks. [src: lexer.aria:151-152]

